  "texts": [
    "Whereas GP begins with random starting populations, the authors in Mundhenk et al. (2021) propose to use the batch of expressions sampled by RNN as a staring population for GP: T (0) GP = T RNN.",
    "Each iteration of the proposed algorithm consists of 4 steps: (1) The batch of expressions sampled by RNN is passed as a starting population to GP, (2) S generations of GP are performed and result in a final GP population T S GP, (3) An elite set of top-performing GP samples is selected T E GP and passed to the gradient update of RNN (Fig. 17",
    "where n can vary across examples, and the number of independent input variables is at most three.",
    "In the test phase, a set of input-output pairs {x i, y i } is fed into the encoder that maps it into a latent vector z, and the",
    "Fig. 18 Taxonomy based on the type of SR benchmark problems decoder iteratively samples candidates' skeletons."
  ]
}